###################################
On an UNIX workstation (ubuntu...)
###################################
    Required:
        mpicc, mpirun, libblas-dev, python (2.7) with numpy and matplotlib

    Make sure that the line "ON_FERLIN=True" is commented in the Makefile

****Check that it works:
        make check

    This should print OK or KO (compile, generate random matrix A and B, run,
    check the results)

    The sizes of the matrices and the number of processors are given in the
    Makefile (I, J, K, PROC_NB). You can check them, but you will need to
    clean if you have already run "make check"
        make clean
        make check

*****Plotting speedup
    ./run.bash

    This should create a directory (result_1000) with a PNG of the speedup for 
    1000*1000 matrices.

###################################
On Ferlin
###################################

    You must add some modules (as usual). But you also need mkl:
        module add mkl 

    Uncomment the line "ON_FERLIN=True"

*****Plotting speedup:
Step 1  On ferlin: ./run_ferlin.bash

        This will create a directory result_5000

Step 2  On a computer with python, numpy and matplotlib, in the directory
        which contains plot_speedup.py

        ./plot_speedup.py result_5000

        This should create a PNG with the speedup


